-- Electronic Arts Said to Sell 15% Stake in Ubisoft
-- Sarah Jones
-- 2010-07-16T06:33:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/electronic-arts-is-selling-15-stake-in-ubisoft-entertainment-terms-show.html

          
          
             Electronic Arts Inc. is selling a 15
percent stake in Ubisoft Entertainment SA, Europe’s biggest
video-game producer, according to terms obtained by Bloomberg
News.  
 UBS AG, the sole bookruner, is placing 14 million Ubisoft
shares at a price range of 6.48 euros to market, the terms show.  
 Electronic Arts is Ubisoft’s largest shareholder, according
to Bloomberg Data. The shares fell 3.2 percent to 6.97 euros in
Paris yesterday.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Ubisoft Entertainment SA chief executive Officer Yves Guillemot. Photographer: Antoine Antoniol/Bloomberg  
                           

     
